ILLINOIS POWER GENERATING COMPANY
POWER SALES TARIFF FOR THE SALE OF ENERGY, CAPACITY AND ANCILLARY SERVICES AT MARKET-BASED RATES
I. Provisions For Wholesale Sales Of Power
1. Availability. Illinois Power Generating Company ( Seller ) shall make electric energy and/or capacity available under this Tariff for wholesale sales to any purchaser for resale, subject to the prohibition set forth in Paragraph 6 below. Seller shall make available under this Tariff ancillary services as set forth in Paragraph 4, below. 2. Applicability. Subject to the provisions of Paragraphs 6 and 8 below, this Tariff is applicable to all sales of electric energy, capacity or ancillary services by Seller, not otherwise subject to a particular Rate Schedule of Seller.
3. Rates. Subject to the provisions of Paragraph 6 below, all sales shall be made at rates negotiated and agreed upon between purchaser and Seller.
4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 5. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 2 seller, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a), with respect to the Central region. Seller is a Category 1 seller, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a), with respect to all other regions.
6. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning a seller s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Seller s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff. 7. Limitations and Exemptions. Seller s market-based rate authority under this Tariff is subject to the following limitations and waivers: (1) waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission s regulations, with the exception of sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16, Ameren Energy Generating Co., 93 FERC 61,024, at 61,046 (2000), and (2) waiver of the accounting and related reporting requirements under Parts 41, 101 and 141 of the Commission s regulations, with the exceptions of sections 141.14 and 141.15. Illinois Power Generating Co., Docket No. ER14-__-000 (______, 2014). Seller has also been granted blanket authorization for the issuance of securities and assumption of liabilities. Ameren Services Co., 132 FERC 61,054 (2010).
8. Ancillary Services: RTO/ISO Specific PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ( PJM ) and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. New York: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc. New England: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc. California: Seller offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation ( CAISO ) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO. MISO: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ( MISO ) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO. Third Party Provider
Third-Party Ancillary Services: Seller offers Regulation Service, Energy Imbalance Service, Spinning Reserves, and Supplemental Reserves. Sales will not include the following: (i) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; (ii) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier; and (iii) sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers. II. The Rate Schedule s Term
1. Duration. This Tariff shall become effective on the date the FERC allows it to become effective and shall continue in effect until terminated pursuant to any applicable order by the FERC. Seller may unilaterally apply to the FERC or other regulatory agency having jurisdiction for a modification or termination of this Tariff under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act and applicable regulations; provided, however, that termination of the Tariff shall not cause the premature termination of any specific transactions entered into prior to the effective date of the termination.

ILLINOIS POWER GENERATING COMPANY
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 6
REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION SOURCES SERVICE
Illinois Power Generating Company (“Seller”) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service (“Reactive Supply Service”) from the listed facilities located in the Ameren Illinois pricing zone in the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc.’s (“MISO”) transmission footprint. This tariff sets forth Seller’s revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Supply Service from the listed facilities pursuant to Schedule 2 of MISO’s Open Access Transmission and Energy Markets Tariff (“TEMT”).
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
Seller’s revenue requirements for the specified facilities shall be calculated as follows:
Newton Power Plant Annual Revenue Requirement $675,000 Monthly Revenue Requirement $56,250
PARTIAL MONTH REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
When a unit deactivation date (“Unit Deactivation Date”) is other than the first day of the month, the revenue requirement shall be a blended revenue requirement for the month of service in which the deactivation occurred as follows: the sum of (i) the total monthly revenue requirement prior to the rate change divided by the number of days in the month of the deactivation, with the quotient then multiplied by the number of days in the month prior to the Unit Deactivation Date and (ii) the total monthly revenue requirement after the rate change divided by the number of days in the month of the deactivation, with the quotient then multiplied by the remaining number of days in the month from and including the Unit Deactivation Date.
